<table class="infobox biography vcard" style="width:22em"><tbody><tr><th colspan="2" style="text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold"><div class="fn" style="display:inline">Sachin Yardi</div></th></tr><tr><th scope="row">Born</th><td><div style="display:inline" class="birthplace"><a href="/wiki/India" title="India">India</a></div></td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Occupation</th><td class="role"><a href="/wiki/Film_director" title="Film director">Film director</a>, <a href="/wiki/Screenwriter" title="Screenwriter">screenwriter</a></td></tr><tr><th scope="row"><span class="nowrap">Spouse(s)</span></th><td><a href="/wiki/Ashvini_Yardi" title="Ashvini Yardi">Ashvini Yardi</a></td></tr></tbody></table>
<p><b>Sachin Yardi</b> is a <a href="/wiki/Hindi_language" class="mw-redirect" title="Hindi language">Hindi</a> <a href="/wiki/Film_director" title="Film director">film director</a> and <a href="/wiki/Screenwriter" title="Screenwriter">screenwriter</a> from <a href="/wiki/India" title="India">India</a>. His <a href="/wiki/Directorial_debut" class="mw-redirect" title="Directorial debut">directorial debut</a> <i><a href="/wiki/C_Kkompany" title="C Kkompany">C Kkompany</a></i> (2008) was after writing scripts for <i><a href="/wiki/Kyaa_Kool_Hai_Hum" title="Kyaa Kool Hai Hum">Kyaa Kool Hai Hum</a></i> (2005) and <a href="/wiki/Madhur_Bhandarkar" title="Madhur Bhandarkar">Madhur Bhandarkar</a>'s award-winning <i><a href="/wiki/Traffic_Signal_(film)" title="Traffic Signal (film)">Traffic Signal</a></i> (2007).<sup id="cite_ref-yardi1_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-yardi1-1">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>
</p>
